<font color="#FF0000">WHAT WE LOST</font><br>
<tt>Sun Mar 16 21:41:24 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Well Arthur what did we lose and how do we recover?  We lost our innocence, but we would have eventually lost that anyway.  We lost dear comrades, but if you've been to the Wall then you know that although those friends are not physically present with us, still because we live they live also, at least in our hearts.  We lost the ability to wholeheartedly trust our government or any other.  Probably, here and now we are starting to seriously deal with that as we find other Americans of like heart and mind.  As you can see I feel that individuals who have successfully integrated the personal loss they suffered in Nam are valuable national assets.  It has to be part of our responsibility to garner the useful aspects of our experience and teach/share with other Americans-especially those younger and less seasoned citizens.  Well Arthur or any other responsible American I look forward to your thoughts.   
